# 🌿 Biomimicry

## What can nature teach us?

Biomimicry is the practice of learning from nature's forms, processes, and systems to solve human challenges.

For billions of years, living organisms have been adapting, evolving, and developing strategies to survive in changing environments. Rather than viewing nature only as a resource, biomimicry explores nature as a source of knowledge, innovation, and inspiration.

This section investigates how plants, ecosystems, and biological systems may inspire future approaches to engineering, sustainability, regenerative design, and environmental problem-solving.

